    <main class="planet-detail" data-planet="neptune">
        <div class="hero-section">
            <img src="../images/neptune.jpg" alt="Neptune" class="hero-image">
            <div class="hero-info">
                <h2>The Windy Giant</h2>
                <p class="hero-description">Neptune is the eighth and farthest known planet from the Sun. It's the windiest planet in our solar system, with wind speeds reaching up to 2,100 km/h, and has the most powerful storms of any planet.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-grid">
            <section class="info-card">
                <h3>Basic Facts</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Type:</strong> Ice Giant</li>
                    <li><strong>Distance from Sun:</strong> 4.5 billion km</li>
                    <li><strong>Diameter:</strong> 49,244 km (3.9 Ã— Earth)</li>
                    <li><strong>Mass:</strong> 1.024 Ã— 10Â²â¶ kg (17 Ã— Earth)</li>
                    <li><strong>Surface Temperature:</strong> -218Â°C (cloud tops)</li>
                    <li><strong>Orbital Period:</strong> 164.8 Earth years</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="info-card">
                <h3>Atmosphere & Weather</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Atmosphere:</strong> Hydrogen (80%), Helium (19%)</li>
                    <li><strong>Methane:</strong> Gives deep blue color</li>
                    <li><strong>Wind Speed:</strong> Up to 2,100 km/h</li>
                    <li><strong>Great Dark Spot:</strong> Giant storm system</li>
                    <li><strong>Storm Duration:</strong> Years to decades</li>
                    <li><strong>Cloud Layers:</strong> Methane, ammonia, water</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="info-card">
                <h3>Internal Structure</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Core:</strong> Rocky core (1.2 Earth masses)</li>
                    <li><strong>Mantle:</strong> Icy mantle (water, ammonia, methane)</li>
                    <li><strong>Atmosphere:</strong> Gaseous hydrogen and helium</li>
                    <li><strong>Density:</strong> 1.64 g/cmÂ³</li>
                    <li><strong>Internal Heat:</strong> Emits 2.6Ã— more than receives</li>
                    <li><strong>Magnetic Field:</strong> 27Ã— stronger than Earth's</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="info-card">
                <h3>Rings & Moons</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Ring System:</strong> 5 main rings</li>
                    <li><strong>Ring Composition:</strong> Dark particles, ice</li>
                    <li><strong>Total Moons:</strong> 16 confirmed</li>
                    <li><strong>Largest Moon:</strong> Triton (captured Kuiper Belt object)</li>
                    <li><strong>Triton:</strong> Retrograde orbit, geysers</li>
                    <li><strong>Moon Names:</strong> Greek mythology</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="info-card">
                <h3>Exploration History</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Discovery:</strong> Mathematical prediction (1846)</li>
                    <li><strong>Voyager 2:</strong> Only flyby (1989)</li>
                    <li><strong>Hubble Space Telescope:</strong> Ongoing observations</li>
                    <li><strong>Ground Telescopes:</strong> Regular monitoring</li>
                    <li><strong>Future Missions:</strong> Proposed orbiters</li>
                    <li><strong>Observation Difficulty:</strong> Very faint from Earth</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="info-card">
                <h3>Unique Characteristics</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Fastest Winds:</strong> 2,100 km/h (supersonic)</li>
                    <li><strong>Internal Heat:</strong> Mysterious heat source</li>
                    <li><strong>Magnetic Field:</strong> Offset from center</li>
                    <li><strong>Storm Systems:</strong> Most powerful in solar system</li>
                    <li><strong>Density:</strong> Highest of the gas giants</li>
                    <li><strong>Orbital Resonance:</strong> Affects Pluto's orbit</li>
                </ul>
            </section>
        </div>

        <section class="fun-facts">
            <h3>Fun Facts</h3>
            <div class="facts-grid">
                <div class="fact">
                    <h4>ğŸ’¨ Windiest Planet</h4>
                    <p>Neptune has the fastest winds in the solar system, reaching speeds of 2,100 km/h - faster than the speed of sound on Earth!</p>
                </div>
                <div class="fact">
                    <h4>ğŸ” Mathematical Discovery</h4>
                    <p>Neptune was the first planet discovered through mathematical calculations rather than direct observation, predicted by Urbain Le Verrier.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="fact">
                    <h4>ğŸŒŠ Triton's Fate</h4>
                    <p>Neptune's largest moon Triton is slowly spiraling inward and will eventually be torn apart by Neptune's gravity in about 3.6 billion years.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="fact">
                    <h4>â„ï¸ Ice Giant</h4>
                    <p>Neptune is called an "ice giant" because its mantle is made of water, ammonia, and methane ices under extreme pressure and temperature.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
