    <header class="header">
        <div class="header-content">
            <a href="index.html" class="back-button">â† Back to Solar System</a>
            <h1>Uranus</h1>
            <p class="subtitle">The Ice Giant - Tilted on Its Side</p>
            <!-- Add to Favorites button will be added by JavaScript -->
        </div>
    </header>
    
    <main class="planet-detail" data-planet="uranus">
        <div class="hero-section">
            <img src="../images/uranus.jpg" alt="Uranus" class="hero-image">
            <div class="hero-info">
                <h2>The Sideways Planet</h2>
                <p class="hero-description">Uranus is the seventh planet from the Sun and the third-largest in the Solar System. It's unique for its extreme axial tilt of 98 degrees, making it appear to rotate on its side.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-grid">
            <section class="info-card">
                <h3>Basic Facts</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Type:</strong> Ice Giant</li>
                    <li><strong>Distance from Sun:</strong> 2.9 billion km</li>
                    <li><strong>Diameter:</strong> 50,724 km (4 Ã— Earth)</li>
                    <li><strong>Mass:</strong> 8.681 Ã— 10Â²âµ kg (14.5 Ã— Earth)</li>
                    <li><strong>Surface Temperature:</strong> -224Â°C (cloud tops)</li>
                    <li><strong>Orbital Period:</strong> 84 Earth years</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="info-card">
                <h3>Unique Tilt & Rotation</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Axial Tilt:</strong> 98 degrees (sideways)</li>
                    <li><strong>Rotation Period:</strong> 17.2 hours</li>
                    <li><strong>Seasons:</strong> 21-year seasons</li>
                    <li><strong>Polar Day/Night:</strong> 42 years each</li>
                    <li><strong>Tilt Cause:</strong> Giant impact theory</li>
                    <li><strong>Magnetic Field:</strong> Offset from center</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="info-card">
                <h3>Atmosphere & Weather</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Atmosphere:</strong> Hydrogen (83%), Helium (15%)</li>
                    <li><strong>Methane:</strong> Gives blue-green color</li>
                    <li><strong>Cloud Layers:</strong> Methane, ammonia, water</li>
                    <li><strong>Wind Speed:</strong> Up to 900 km/h</li>
                    <li><strong>Storm Systems:</strong> Dark spots and storms</li>
                    <li><strong>Temperature:</strong> Coldest planet in solar system</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="info-card">
                <h3>Internal Structure</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Core:</strong> Rocky core (0.5 Earth masses)</li>
                    <li><strong>Mantle:</strong> Icy mantle (water, ammonia, methane)</li>
                    <li><strong>Atmosphere:</strong> Gaseous hydrogen and helium</li>
                    <li><strong>Density:</strong> 1.27 g/cmÂ³</li>
                    <li><strong>Internal Heat:</strong> Very low heat emission</li>
                    <li><strong>Magnetic Field:</strong> Tilted 60 degrees</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="info-card">
                <h3>Rings & Moons</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Ring System:</strong> 13 faint rings</li>
                    <li><strong>Ring Composition:</strong> Dark particles, ice</li>
                    <li><strong>Total Moons:</strong> 27 confirmed</li>
                    <li><strong>Largest Moons:</strong> Titania, Oberon, Umbriel</li>
                    <li><strong>Moon Names:</strong> Shakespeare characters</li>
                    <li><strong>Shepherd Moons:</strong> Maintain ring structure</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="info-card">
                <h3>Exploration History</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Discovery:</strong> William Herschel (1781)</li>
                    <li><strong>Voyager 2:</strong> Only flyby (1986)</li>
                    <li><strong>Hubble Space Telescope:</strong> Ongoing observations</li>
                    <li><strong>Ground Telescopes:</strong> Regular monitoring</li>
                    <li><strong>Future Missions:</strong> Proposed orbiters</li>
                    <li><strong>Observation Difficulty:</strong> Faint from Earth</li>
                </ul>
            </section>
        </div>

        <section class="fun-facts">
            <h3>Fun Facts</h3>
            <div class="facts-grid">
                <div class="fact">
                    <h4>ğŸ”„ Sideways Spin</h4>
                    <p>Uranus rotates on its side with an axial tilt of 98 degrees, making it the only planet that rolls like a ball.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="fact">
                    <h4>â„ï¸ Coldest Planet</h4>
                    <p>Uranus is the coldest planet in the solar system, with temperatures dropping to -224Â°C, even colder than Neptune.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="fact">
                    <h4>ğŸŒ™ Literary Moons</h4>
                    <p>All of Uranus' 27 moons are named after characters from the works of William Shakespeare and Alexander Pope.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="fact">
                    <h4>ğŸ’ Ice Giant</h4>
                    <p>Uranus is called an "ice giant" because its mantle is made of water, ammonia, and methane ices under high pressure.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
