    <header class="header">
        <div class="header-content">
            <a href="index.html" class="back-button">â† Back to Solar System</a>
            <h1>Venus</h1>
            <p class="subtitle">The Hottest Planet - Earth's Twin</p>
            <!-- Add to Favorites button will be added by JavaScript -->
        </div>
    </header>
    
    <main class="planet-detail" data-planet="venus">
        <div class="hero-section">
            <img src="../images/venus.jpg" alt="Venus" class="hero-image">
            <div class="hero-info">
                <h2>The Morning Star</h2>
                <p class="hero-description">Venus is the second planet from the Sun and Earth's closest planetary neighbor. It's often called Earth's twin due to similar size, but its extreme greenhouse effect makes it the hottest planet in our solar system.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="content-grid">
            <section class="info-card">
                <h3>Basic Facts</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Type:</strong> Terrestrial Planet</li>
                    <li><strong>Distance from Sun:</strong> 108.2 million km</li>
                    <li><strong>Diameter:</strong> 12,104 km (0.95 Ã— Earth)</li>
                    <li><strong>Mass:</strong> 4.867 Ã— 10Â²â´ kg (0.815 Ã— Earth)</li>
                    <li><strong>Surface Temperature:</strong> 462Â°C (average)</li>
                    <li><strong>Orbital Period:</strong> 224.7 Earth days</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="info-card">
                <h3>Atmosphere & Climate</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Atmosphere:</strong> Carbon dioxide (96.5%)</li>
                    <li><strong>Surface Pressure:</strong> 92 atm (93 times Earth)</li>
                    <li><strong>Greenhouse Effect:</strong> Extreme runaway effect</li>
                    <li><strong>Clouds:</strong> Sulfuric acid droplets</li>
                    <li><strong>Wind Speed:</strong> Up to 360 km/h</li>
                    <li><strong>Visibility:</strong> Completely obscured by clouds</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="info-card">
                <h3>Surface Features</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Volcanoes:</strong> 1,600+ major volcanoes</li>
                    <li><strong>Mountains:</strong> Maxwell Montes (11 km high)</li>
                    <li><strong>Plains:</strong> 70% of surface covered</li>
                    <li><strong>Craters:</strong> Few due to thick atmosphere</li>
                    <li><strong>Coronae:</strong> Circular volcanic features</li>
                    <li><strong>Tesserae:</strong> Complex ridged terrain</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="info-card">
                <h3>Composition & Structure</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Core:</strong> Iron-nickel core</li>
                    <li><strong>Mantle:</strong> Silicate rock layer</li>
                    <li><strong>Crust:</strong> Basaltic composition</li>
                    <li><strong>Surface Age:</strong> 300-600 million years</li>
                    <li><strong>Density:</strong> 5.24 g/cmÂ³</li>
                    <li><strong>Internal Heat:</strong> Active volcanism</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="info-card">
                <h3>Exploration History</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Mariner 2:</strong> First flyby (1962)</li>
                    <li><strong>Venera Program:</strong> Soviet landers (1961-1984)</li>
                    <li><strong>Magellan:</strong> Radar mapping (1990-1994)</li>
                    <li><strong>Venus Express:</strong> ESA orbiter (2006-2014)</li>
                    <li><strong>Akatsuki:</strong> Japanese orbiter (2015-)</li>
                    <li><strong>Future Missions:</strong> DAVINCI+, VERITAS</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="info-card">
                <h3>Unique Characteristics</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Retrograde Rotation:</strong> Spins backwards</li>
                    <li><strong>Solar Day:</strong> 117 Earth days</li>
                    <li><strong>Year Length:</strong> 225 Earth days</li>
                    <li><strong>No Moons:</strong> No natural satellites</li>
                    <li><strong>Brightest Planet:</strong> Visible to naked eye</li>
                    <li><strong>Phase Changes:</strong> Like the Moon</li>
                </ul>
            </section>
        </div>

        <section class="fun-facts">
            <h3>Fun Facts</h3>
            <div class="facts-grid">
                <div class="fact">
                    <h4>ğŸ”¥ Hottest Planet</h4>
                    <p>Venus is hotter than Mercury despite being farther from the Sun, due to its extreme greenhouse effect.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="fact">
                    <h4>ğŸŒªï¸ Backwards Spin</h4>
                    <p>Venus rotates backwards compared to most planets, with its axis tilted at 177 degrees.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="fact">
                    <h4>â˜ï¸ Acid Clouds</h4>
                    <p>Venus has clouds made of sulfuric acid that rain acid, but it evaporates before reaching the surface.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="fact">
                    <h4>â­ Morning Star</h4>
                    <p>Venus is the brightest object in the night sky after the Moon, visible before sunrise and after sunset.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
